aws as to maximum benefits duration of benefit payments waiting pe riods before payments start and extent of coverage is indicated by current state legislative develop ments throughout the country Such a trend has been In prog ress ever since the inception of these laws but it was especially accelerated last year While com paratively few legislatures convene in regular session this year it ap pears likely that a number of them as well as some meeting in special sessions will further liberalize un employment compensation statutes This action which probably will be taken on a more wide spread basis next year when some 43 state legislatures will again meet in regular session results to a considerable extent from belief that liberalisation of the state laws will lessen pressure for federal control of the entire unemployment compensation sys tem With state unemployment reserve funds now approximating a total of 7 billion compared with less than 2 billion in early 1941 it 1r generally agreed that liberalization as to maximum payments duration of"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-01-16T21:41:42.215Z", "group": ["ndnp/mimtptc", "central-michigan-university-clark-historical-library-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/77618337/1946-02-18/ed-1/?sp=22", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mimtptc:batch_mimtptc_jerome_ver02:data:77618337:00414188199:1946021801:1290/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=395&w=289", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mimtptc:batch_mimtptc_jerome_ver02:data:77618337:00414188199:1946021801:1290/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=790&w=579", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/mimtptc/batch_mimtptc_jerome_ver02/data/77618337/00414188199/1946021801/1290.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 22, "language": ["english"], "location": ["wayne", "michigan", "united states", "detroit"], "location_city": ["detroit"], "location_count